485 761 dQL ; -LRB- fb -RRB- dQL ; dUR ; By CONSTANCE L. HAYS dQC ; dLR ; dQL ; dUR ; c. 1998 N.Y. Times News Service dLR ; dQC ; dQL ; At the Container Store , a Dallas-based chain that specializes in storage products and closet organizers , employees do far more than ring up sales .
762 991 They are trained to think of themselves as counselors or problem-solvers _ whether the issue is a shared closet that must house one spouse 's 34 pairs of shoes or a child 's room spilling over with an unmanageable number of toys .
992 1131 `` We 've had customers come up to us and say , ` This is better than a visit to my shrink , '' ' said Garrett Boone , the chief executive .
1132 1342 The company , which has 19 stores around the country , considers customer service a `` core competency , '' not a frill , and trains sales clerks for 185 hours the first year ; the industry average is below 10 .
1343 1486 And the company often hires its best customers , maintaining that people who are not actively looking for a job turn out to be great employees .
1487 1552 But the Container Store 's approach , alas , is a rare exception .
1553 1706 For most of America , customer service frequently remains an oxymoron , though there are signs that some stores are paying more attention to the problem .
1707 1892 Staffs have been cut in the heat of competitive battle , and sales clerks who remain are often less than stellar _ since with joblessness down , good workers have higher-paying options .
1893 1988 And while this is a year-round problem , it is especially acute in the frenzied holiday season .
1989 2106 At this time of year , hordes of shoppers confront temporary sales clerks , who may be the least well trained of all .
2107 2199 Judging from shoppers ' stories , many encounters with sales `` help '' turn decidedly sour .
2200 2318 When customers do have a good experience , it must seem like a rarity , for they often feel compelled to remark on it .
2319 2435 As gauged by a University of Michigan index , customer-service satisfaction has dropped steadily the last few years .
2436 2654 The rate of satisfaction among the 200,000 shoppers interviewed remains far below what it was in 1994 , said Claes Fornell , a professor of business administration who oversees the American Customer Satisfaction Index .
2655 2839 `` You have fewer people serving more customers , '' he said , adding that he has had his own run-ins with airlines and cable companies , `` and the result is usually worse service . ''
2840 2932 Some stores that have had cutbacks have little to offer workers in terms of training or pay .
2933 3003 Others have apparently failed to anticipate what customers might need .
3004 3272 `` I was at one store that had good service , to the point that the guy kind of hovered around me , '' said Inna Hagen , an actress and lawyer in New York City , `` but then they did n't have gift wrap , which was annoying when you 're shopping for Christmas presents .
3273 3306 They charged me $ 6 for a ribbon .
3307 3403 `` I expect good service , '' she added , `` but I think you do n't get it a lot of the time . ''
3404 3619 At the Container Store , `` We know we are just wild-eyed fanatics when it comes to human resources and training , '' said Kip Tindell , the chief operating officer , who founded the company with Boone 20 years ago .
3620 3742 `` It is the most difficult and the most joyous part of the retail business , and most people avoid it like the plague . ''
3743 3862 The company says it makes a hefty profit , too , though it is privately held and does not make such information public .
3863 4156 Service Intelligence , an Atlanta consulting firm that is hired to place spies _ or `` mystery shoppers , '' as they prefer to call them _ in stores to see how well managed everything is , has a Web site -LRB- www.serviceintelligence.com -RRB- stocked with horror stories sent in by consumers .
4157 4221 Some of the most outrageous incidents occurred in retail stores .
4222 4369 `` While visiting a department store , I was amazed at how the only sales clerk in the area was chatting on the telephone , '' a consumer reported .
