4747 4901 Much of the deterioration is the result of price wars , which prompted one executive after another to zero in on customer service as an expendable luxury .
4902 5200 `` It 's been a huge mistake for many of these retailers , '' said Leonard L. Berry , a professor at Texas AdAMP ; M University 's Center for Retailing Studies , who is about to publish a book , `` Discovering the Soul of Service , '' which examines businesses that have effective customer service .
