5782 5955 In many cases , the nation 's low unemployment rate has propelled would-be retail workers into higher-paying jobs elsewhere , leaving few options for stores that are hiring .
5956 6086 `` The big story this year is the employment crunch , '' said Bruce Van Kleeck , vice president of the National Retail Federation .
6087 6291 `` It 's been challenging for three years , but this year is by far the worst , because this terrific economic situation the United States has been enjoying has been a double-edged sword for retailers . ''
6292 6357 That does not make shoppers any more sympathetic to sales clerks .
6358 6641 `` The great majority of them are either totally incompetent or they need complete attitude adjustment because they think they are better than the customer , '' said Anne Goldrach of New York City , whose experiences made shopping on the Internet that much more attractive this year .
